<section class="section section--tight" aria-labelledby="funding-heading">
  <div class="container prose">
    <h2 id="funding-heading">Your PAC may already have the budget</h2>
    <p>School gardens in BC are more fundable than most PACs realize. Two paths cover most programs:</p>
    <details>
      <summary>Farm to School BC grants</summary>
      <p>Farm to School BC offers grants that fund school food-growing and food-literacy projects. Expressions of interest typically open early in the calendar year — worth checking farmtoschoolbc.ca for the current cycle before planning a spring build.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>PAC Community Gaming Grants</summary>
      <p>BC PACs receive $20 per student in Community Gaming funds (application window April 1 – June 30). Framed as extracurricular, experiential learning, a garden program is a strong fit for these funds — and we can help with the framing.</p>
    </details>
    <p>Practical timing: talk to your PAC in spring, build in late summer or fall, plant the next spring.</p>
  </div>
</section>

